<h2><a href="http://www.cs.dartmouth.edu/robotcamp">Summer Robotics Program, 2009</a></h2>
<h2>Camp 1: Building Robots (<a href="iweb/index.html">Pictures!</a>)</h2>

<b>When</b>:
June 22 (Monday) - June 26 (Friday). 9am-noon Mon-Thu, and Friday will be
a field trip.

<br />

<b>Where</b>:
<a href="http://engineering.dartmouth.edu/">Thayer School of Engineering,</a>
<a href="http://www.dartmouth.edu/">Dartmouth College</a>

<br />
<br />

In this camp we will apply engineering principles while building a robot.
See our
<a href="poster.pdf">poster</a> for the Summer Robotics program this year.

<h4>Schedule</h4>
<ul>
    <li><bf>Day 1</bf>. Assemble a robot:  We will build a line-crawler robot
    from pre-built parts.
    </li>
    <li><bf>Day 2</bf>. Breadboarding: Build the circuit for the line-crawler
    on a breadboard.</li>
    <li><bf>Day 3</bf>. Printed Circuit Boards: Build the circuit by soldering
    components onto a circuit board.</li>
    <li><bf>Day 4</bf>. Fabrication: Assemble all components and make them run.
    </li>
    <li><bf>Day 5</bf>. Field trip to the
    <a href="http://www.americanprecision.org/">American Precision Museum.</a>
    </li>
</ul>

<h4>Reference Text</h4>
<a href="http://www.robotroom.com/RBFB.html">"Robot Building for Beginners,"</a>
David Cook.

